WEBVTT

00:02.303 --> 00:05.273
Look what I found in the fridge,
a lovely rosÃ©.

00:05.306 --> 00:06.774
Or a pink lemonade
that went bad.

00:06.807 --> 00:08.042
Either way,
it's doing the trick.

00:08.076 --> 00:09.477
What are we drinking to?

00:09.510 --> 00:11.545
Hmm, nine days
without freaking out

00:11.579 --> 00:13.647
about your committed
relationship?

00:13.681 --> 00:16.517
It would've been 14 if Andy
hadn't texted me that night.

00:16.550 --> 00:17.818
Ben's kids really should not
be texting me yet.

00:17.851 --> 00:19.520
It's way too fast.

00:19.553 --> 00:22.256
And the freak-out calendar
is back to zero.

00:22.290 --> 00:24.692
Uh-oh.
Nice one, blondie.

00:24.725 --> 00:26.560
Uh-oh, now it's your turn
to freak out.
[ Scoffs ]

00:26.594 --> 00:27.828
I don't freak out
about anything.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.263
Really?
'Cause I remember

00:29.297 --> 00:31.432
a certain game
we used to play as kids.

00:31.465 --> 00:35.169
You are very scared
of vacuums.

00:35.203 --> 00:36.770
No, I'm not. Shut up. You are.
[ Vacuum whirring ]

00:36.804 --> 00:38.539
I just like dirt
'cause dirt is cool,

00:38.572 --> 00:40.308
and -- and I'm cool.
[ Laughs ]

00:40.341 --> 00:41.642
Hey! Get that thing
away from me! Come on!

00:41.675 --> 00:42.676
Okay? This isn't funny.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.678
Okay, I'm over here.
No, I'm not.

00:44.712 --> 00:46.180
Okay. [ Grunts ]

00:46.214 --> 00:47.481
[ Laughs ]

00:47.515 --> 00:48.649
I feel like relaxing
over here. Just...

00:48.682 --> 00:49.817
Leave me alone.
Just, I-I...

00:49.850 --> 00:51.319
Got you.

00:51.352 --> 00:53.254
No, I'm not. Okay.
[ Shouts ]

00:53.287 --> 00:55.856
Okay, okay, I'm scared
of vacuums! Turn it off!

00:55.889 --> 00:57.225
[ Shouts ]
[ Vacuum stops ]

00:57.258 --> 00:59.527
[ Sighs ]
No, I'm not.

00:59.560 --> 01:00.828
[ Scoffs ]
Yes, I am!
I'm scared! I'm scared!

01:00.861 --> 01:02.730
[ Vacuum whirring ]
Alice: Ha!

01:02.763 --> 01:04.031
Mary: This is Alice.

01:04.064 --> 01:06.734
When she was a kid, she
dreamed up me to be her BFF.

01:06.767 --> 01:09.137
Now my girl
has finally fallen in love,

01:09.170 --> 01:11.739
but she's in way over her head,
so I'm back to help.

01:11.772 --> 01:13.607
I've got this all figured out.

01:13.641 --> 01:16.777
No, you don't.
No, I don't.

01:16.810 --> 01:18.679
Okay, before we watch
the next episode,

01:18.712 --> 01:20.514
you need to know
that in Season 12,

01:20.548 --> 01:22.250
Kiki thought she fell
in love with Damon,

01:22.283 --> 01:23.717
but now Damon,
according to US Weekly,

01:23.751 --> 01:26.254
is marrying the makeup
artist from Season 6,

01:26.287 --> 01:28.389
which makes perfect sense 'cause
when someone touches your face

01:28.422 --> 01:29.723
and makes you beautiful,
you're like,

01:29.757 --> 01:31.159
"Yeah, I'll spend
my life with you."

01:31.192 --> 01:33.194
Aw, poor Kiki.

01:33.227 --> 01:34.762
And a little bit poor you.

01:34.795 --> 01:36.664
The heart wants
what the heart wants,

01:36.697 --> 01:39.667
and my heart wants this show.

01:39.700 --> 01:41.735
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

01:41.769 --> 01:43.137
Darn it!

01:43.171 --> 01:44.572
Strong language.

01:44.605 --> 01:46.574
No, I forgot Zoe was having
a party tonight.

01:46.607 --> 01:48.309
I'll just tell her
I can't make it.

01:48.342 --> 01:49.643
Which one is Zoe?
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:49.677 --> 01:50.911
A friend.

01:50.944 --> 01:52.646
Well, I've never met
any of your friends,

01:52.680 --> 01:54.215
so can you give me
a little more?

01:54.248 --> 01:55.883
I met her through Rebecca.

01:55.916 --> 01:57.685
And Rebecca is?

01:57.718 --> 01:58.786
Zoe's friend.

02:00.488 --> 02:02.823
Hey, you two.
What are we doing?

02:02.856 --> 02:05.226
Normally, I'd be partying hard
with my friend Jeff,

02:05.259 --> 02:06.360
but he just moved away.

02:06.394 --> 02:07.728
Aw. That's hard.

02:07.761 --> 02:09.763
Not as hard as Jeff and I
used to party.

02:09.797 --> 02:10.898
Why don't you call
your friend Finn?

02:10.931 --> 02:12.200
Oh, we're just
lab partners.

02:12.233 --> 02:13.901
We don't mix
science and pleasure.

02:13.934 --> 02:15.736
Right.

02:15.769 --> 02:17.638
Hey, Andy, Alice and I are
just finishing up something,

02:17.671 --> 02:18.906
but I'll come find you
in a minute.

02:18.939 --> 02:20.374
Got it.
Yeah.

02:20.408 --> 02:22.876
**

02:22.910 --> 02:24.945
I'll come find you.

02:24.978 --> 02:26.947
In your room.

02:26.980 --> 02:29.217
Double got it.

02:32.453 --> 02:33.854
You got an ETA on that or...?

02:35.756 --> 02:38.592
We'll call it a soft 10.

02:38.626 --> 02:41.962
I really do need to help
that kid make some new friends.
[ Laughs ]

02:41.995 --> 02:43.497
You know how Dora
is never around

02:43.531 --> 02:44.498
and never tells me anything?

02:44.532 --> 02:46.200
I need Andy to be
more like that.

02:46.234 --> 02:48.202
I think it's sweet how
you're always there for him.

02:48.236 --> 02:49.470
You're like his
best friend.

02:49.503 --> 02:51.239
Oh, okay, I see
the problem.

02:51.272 --> 02:52.306
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

02:52.340 --> 02:54.542
Zoe again?

02:54.575 --> 02:56.810
No, now it's Rebecca, hounding
me about skipping the party.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

02:56.844 --> 02:58.879
[ Sighs ]
You know...

02:58.912 --> 03:01.249
maybe the party doesn't
have to be skipped.

03:01.282 --> 03:03.917
Aw, you're so sweet, but I don't
want to leave you home alone.

03:03.951 --> 03:05.553
Where's the remote?

03:05.586 --> 03:07.988
Well, in my scenario,
I wouldn't be home alone.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.390
Oh, you'd be with Andy?

03:09.423 --> 03:11.792
No, 'cause I'd go
to the party.

03:11.825 --> 03:13.327
And I'd stay with Andy?

03:13.361 --> 03:15.729
There's an option
you're not considering.

03:17.298 --> 03:19.533
We can go together.

03:19.567 --> 03:21.435
Mary: Oh, no.
We do not mix worlds.

03:21.469 --> 03:23.504
When worlds collide,
no one survives.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.472
Ask the dinosaurs.

03:24.505 --> 03:27.341
Oh! Distract him
with some Frenching.
Um, I...

03:27.375 --> 03:28.876
I said get to Frenching,
woman!

03:32.513 --> 03:34.648
I like what this show
does to you,

03:34.682 --> 03:35.983
but I feel like you're
avoiding the issue.
Mm-hmm.

03:36.016 --> 03:37.585
You know what I love?

03:37.618 --> 03:39.320
I love that you
know me so well

03:39.353 --> 03:40.821
you know when I'm
avoiding an issue.

03:40.854 --> 03:42.690
Okay. Okay.

03:42.723 --> 03:44.692
Is there a reason you don't
want to take advantage

03:44.725 --> 03:46.026
of this very
convenient opportunity

03:46.059 --> 03:47.328
for me to meet
your friends?

03:47.361 --> 03:48.596
Or is this just
your usual fear

03:48.629 --> 03:50.398
of emotional hurdles
and deepening commitment?

03:50.431 --> 03:51.399
The uzhe.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.033
That's my girl.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.035
Well, when you are ready,
just know that I'd love

03:55.068 --> 03:56.637
to get to know
the people in your life.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.572
Okay.

03:58.606 --> 04:00.708
[ Click,
indistinct talking on TV ]

04:00.741 --> 04:02.876
FYI,
I'm happy to meet Ben

04:02.910 --> 04:04.945
whenever you feel
the time is right.

04:04.978 --> 04:05.979
[ Grunts ]
[ Thud ]

04:06.013 --> 04:08.048
Left, right. Left, right.

04:08.081 --> 04:09.417
Sorry I missed the party.
Was it fun?

04:09.450 --> 04:10.518
It was
the most amazing party.

04:10.551 --> 04:11.885
It was fine.

04:11.919 --> 04:13.321
It was okay.

04:13.354 --> 04:14.522
I get that when your
friends disappear

04:14.555 --> 04:16.056
to marriage
and motherhood,

04:16.089 --> 04:17.858
you have to restock
but, uh, these two?

04:17.891 --> 04:19.627
You could've shopped around
a little longer, right?

04:19.660 --> 04:20.894
[ Laughs ]

04:20.928 --> 04:22.062
Ooh. Ow, ow, ow!

04:22.095 --> 04:24.632
Instructor:
Good. One, two. One, two.

04:24.665 --> 04:25.633
So, why didn't
you make the party?

04:25.666 --> 04:27.368
I was hanging
out with Ben.

04:27.401 --> 04:28.669
You know,
you could've brought him.

04:28.702 --> 04:31.439
Oh, really? Oh, I didn't
know he was invited.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.341
Oh, that's my bad. Maybe my text
wasn't clear enough.

04:33.374 --> 04:34.575
You know,
the one that said,

04:34.608 --> 04:36.310
"Bring Ben.
We'd love to meet him."

04:36.344 --> 04:38.579
It's hard to read tone in text.
I heard it as

04:38.612 --> 04:41.682
[ Sarcastically ] "Bring Ben.
We'd love to meet him."

04:41.715 --> 04:44.017
Alice, seriously,
we want to meet your boyfriend.

04:44.051 --> 04:46.920
Okay, seriously, I would like
to put that off for a while.

04:46.954 --> 04:48.956
Not a big fan of
mixing worlds.

04:48.989 --> 04:52.526
**

04:52.560 --> 04:54.462
Look, the first time I did
something like that with Ben

04:54.495 --> 04:56.597
was when I met his kids,
and it almost broke us up.

04:56.630 --> 04:57.931
We're in a really
good place right now,

04:57.965 --> 04:58.932
and I just want to stay here.

04:58.966 --> 05:02.002
For the record,
Ben is cool with it, too. So...

05:02.035 --> 05:04.071
Can I just get serious
with you for a second,

05:04.104 --> 05:05.072
as your best friend?

05:05.105 --> 05:06.907
Best friend?! Who dis?

05:06.940 --> 05:08.409
Ben might say
that he's okay with it,

05:08.442 --> 05:09.577
but that doesn't mean
that he is.

05:09.610 --> 05:11.011
I mean, meeting friends
is pretty standard.

05:11.044 --> 05:12.680
And if you're not
willing to do

05:12.713 --> 05:15.616
the basic stuff,
then this guy could bolt.

05:15.649 --> 05:17.050
[ Laughs ] Bolting?
This guy's got three kids

05:17.084 --> 05:18.919
dragging from his ankles.
He's not bolting anywhere.

05:18.952 --> 05:20.988
Are you serious?
Something to think about.

05:21.021 --> 05:22.723
-Very serious.
-Dead serious.

05:22.756 --> 05:24.492
She said she didn't
want to mix worlds.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.093
Best friend?

05:26.126 --> 05:27.595
More like "worst friend
of all time" friend.

05:27.628 --> 05:29.062
Ben's not gonna
break up with me

05:29.096 --> 05:31.632
just because I want to keep
my worlds a little separate.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.468
If Damon can leave
someone like Kiki,

05:34.502 --> 05:36.704
anything can happen.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.105
Instructor:
Good. One, two.

05:38.138 --> 05:40.841
**

05:40.874 --> 05:43.577
Bunny, Madison's mom
is here to pick you up!

05:43.611 --> 05:46.714
Girl takes
the longest peepees.

05:46.747 --> 05:49.450
I am so happy we've finally been
able to schedule a playdate.

05:49.483 --> 05:51.685
Seems like Bunny's been
in high demand lately.

05:51.719 --> 05:53.587
She's on a good run.

05:53.621 --> 05:54.988
Three trips to the aquarium
in one week --

05:55.022 --> 05:57.057
That's got to be
some kind of record.

05:57.090 --> 05:58.959
Hi, Madison With
the Brown Hair's mom.

05:58.992 --> 06:01.729
No, I'm Madison With
the Blond Hair's mom.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.097
Oh, good.
I like her better.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.766
Hey, you have
an older son, right?

06:05.799 --> 06:07.134
Yeah, Mike.

06:07.167 --> 06:09.002
Maybe we can set something up
for Mike and Andy?

06:09.036 --> 06:10.438
[ Laughs ]

06:10.471 --> 06:12.005
Good one.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.442
Can you imagine? Setting a
playdate for our teenagers?

06:14.475 --> 06:16.009
[ Laughs ]

06:16.043 --> 06:17.645
[ Laughs ]

06:17.678 --> 06:18.912
Yeah, no,
that would be insane.

06:18.946 --> 06:20.681
That's something Madison
With the Brown Hair's mom

06:20.714 --> 06:21.682
would suggest.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.116
She's the worst.

06:23.150 --> 06:24.017
I know. I was joking.

06:24.051 --> 06:25.853
[ Laughs ]

06:25.886 --> 06:28.088
[ Door opens ]

06:28.121 --> 06:29.490
[ Door closes ]

06:29.523 --> 06:31.659
Hey, Dora.
Yeah?

06:31.692 --> 06:33.761
You know Andy's friend Jeff
moved away, right?

06:33.794 --> 06:36.129
And that Andy's having
a tough time with it?
Nope. Okay, bye.

06:36.163 --> 06:38.866
No, no, no. Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa. Sweetie.

06:38.899 --> 06:41.168
Ever notice how most of us
hide our weirdness

06:41.201 --> 06:42.503
and don't reveal
our true selves

06:42.536 --> 06:43.737
until after
we've made friends?

06:43.771 --> 06:45.739
Andy leads with his weird.

06:45.773 --> 06:47.541
I mean, in a perfect world,

06:47.575 --> 06:49.109
he'd be revered
for his emotional honesty,

06:49.142 --> 06:50.744
but that's not
the world we live in.

06:50.778 --> 06:52.480
Yeah, no, I-I get
what you're asking.

06:52.513 --> 06:55.583
And, hey, you know, in a --
in a perfect world,

06:55.616 --> 06:58.786
I would love to help Andy make
friends, but as you pointed out,

06:58.819 --> 07:00.788
it's not perfect,
so...bye.

07:00.821 --> 07:02.122
Whoa. No, no.
Oh, look!

07:02.155 --> 07:04.492
[ Gasps ]
Your girlfriend's here.

07:04.525 --> 07:06.594
You should talk to
her instead of me.

07:06.627 --> 07:07.961
[ Sighs ]

07:07.995 --> 07:09.730
Hi, babe.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.098
Why are you listening
to those girls?

07:11.131 --> 07:12.633
He is not gonna
break up with you

07:12.666 --> 07:13.734
if he doesn't
meet your friends.

07:13.767 --> 07:15.135
I want you
to meet my friends.

07:15.168 --> 07:16.504
[ Groans ]
Why am I even here?

07:16.537 --> 07:18.005
Shut up. Really?

07:18.038 --> 07:20.941
Mixing worlds is fun.
It's normal. I can do it.

07:20.974 --> 07:22.676
Great. Let's set something up.
Yeah.

07:22.710 --> 07:24.478
Tomorrow.
Okay, even better.

07:24.512 --> 07:25.979
Cool. Don't talk
me out of it.

07:26.013 --> 07:28.048
**

07:28.081 --> 07:29.783
Okay.

07:34.888 --> 07:37.491
[ Sighs ] Why didn't you
talk me out of it?

07:37.525 --> 07:38.692
Oh, don't you dare.

07:43.531 --> 07:44.498
[ Sighs ] What did I do?
Why did I invite Ben

07:44.532 --> 07:45.966
to meet my friends?
Mary: That's what you get

07:45.999 --> 07:47.535
when you listen
to your worst friend, Rebecca.

07:47.568 --> 07:48.702
[ Coughs ]
Whore.

07:48.736 --> 07:50.971
And not
your best friend, me.

07:51.004 --> 07:53.807
There are so many ways

07:53.841 --> 07:55.676
this mixing of worlds
could go wrong.

07:55.709 --> 07:58.879
What if my friends think
he's a boring suburban dad,

07:58.912 --> 08:00.247
and then I start thinking
he's a boring suburban dad,

08:00.280 --> 08:01.615
and then we break up?

08:01.649 --> 08:02.983
Scenario is highly likely.

08:03.016 --> 08:04.852
Wouldn't kill the guy
to jazz it up a bit.

08:04.885 --> 08:06.053
What if they have
nothing in common?

08:06.086 --> 08:08.656
What if Ben thinks they're a
couple of millennial ding-dongs,

08:08.689 --> 08:10.558
which makes him start
looking differently at me,

08:10.591 --> 08:12.059
which then leads him
to breaking up with me?

08:12.092 --> 08:14.294
Well, that's a pretty
real possibility.

08:14.327 --> 08:16.897
'Cause those two are 10 out
of 10 on the ding-dong scale.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.666
It's official, then.

08:18.699 --> 08:19.967
12 hours until
I'm single again.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.669
Look, if you
really like him...

08:21.702 --> 08:23.103
I really do.

08:23.136 --> 08:24.705
All right, keep it
in your pants.

08:24.738 --> 08:25.839
Here's what we do.

08:25.873 --> 08:29.677
We find a way these worlds
can mix without really mixing.

08:29.710 --> 08:31.879
Yes. Exactly. How?
That makes no sense.

08:31.912 --> 08:33.714
Remember after
your parents split?

08:33.747 --> 08:35.115
Once a year, they'd take you out
for your birthday

08:35.148 --> 08:36.884
and they'd somehow get through
the night without anyone

08:36.917 --> 08:38.852
getting yelled at,
ticked off, or stabbed.

08:38.886 --> 08:39.720
They only
stabbed each other once.

08:39.753 --> 08:41.922
It was not at my birthday party.
Exactly.

08:41.955 --> 08:42.990
'Cause the restaurant
we always went to

08:43.023 --> 08:45.926
was too loud, too distracting,
and too damn wonderful

08:45.959 --> 08:47.327
for anyone to even talk
to each other.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.896
Never mind stab each other.

08:48.929 --> 08:51.064
**

08:51.098 --> 08:53.834
My worlds can mix
without mixing at all.

08:53.867 --> 08:56.269
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:58.238 --> 08:59.740
So...

09:01.609 --> 09:03.343
Right this way.

09:03.376 --> 09:04.745
This okay?

09:04.778 --> 09:06.213
Oh, it's okay.
We can move over.

09:06.246 --> 09:08.081
No, no, no. Please, please,
please, do not move.

09:08.115 --> 09:09.917
We don't want
to inconvenience you.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.619
You're our nation's
greatest treasure.

09:11.652 --> 09:12.586
You guys sit there.

09:12.620 --> 09:13.821
Wait, um...

09:13.854 --> 09:15.088
Over here?

09:15.122 --> 09:17.090
Why...couldn't we do that?

09:17.124 --> 09:19.126
I think it's gonna be a
little hard for us to talk.

09:19.159 --> 09:21.261
Shh. Babe, look,
he's chopping onions.

09:21.294 --> 09:23.063
This is my favorite part.

09:23.096 --> 09:24.297
* She's in part of my brain...

09:24.331 --> 09:26.867
Yeah, magical.
[ Chuckles ]

09:26.900 --> 09:28.769
So, Rebecca...

09:28.802 --> 09:31.839
Hold up, here come the peppers.
These are my second favorite.

09:31.872 --> 09:33.240
* I catch up right

09:33.273 --> 09:36.877
* To find the one, oh

09:36.910 --> 09:39.379
* I can't stop, I can...

09:39.412 --> 09:41.348
Fun, huh?

09:41.381 --> 09:43.050
So, Ben, Alice says
you're a contractor.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.918
What do you work on?
Shrimp us!

09:45.753 --> 09:47.087
Yeah!

09:48.088 --> 09:48.956
Ben: Hey!

09:50.057 --> 09:51.825
Oh. [ Laughs ]

09:51.859 --> 09:53.226
That shrimp just hit me
in the face, Alice.

09:53.260 --> 09:54.928
* No, I can't...

09:54.962 --> 09:57.397
Yay.
Alice: Bravo.

09:57.430 --> 09:59.833
I'm not gonna clap.

09:59.867 --> 10:01.869
Wait. Do you guys
not hear that?

10:01.902 --> 10:03.971
It's the sound of a thousand
knives not being banged.

10:04.004 --> 10:05.906
So we can talk now.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.040
We have to
take advantage.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.876
Yeah, Ben,
you either said

10:08.909 --> 10:10.310
that you went to college
or that you liked collage.

10:10.343 --> 10:12.145
FYI, I approve of both.

10:12.179 --> 10:14.281
Well, interesting story.
Um, I actually applied...

10:14.314 --> 10:17.918
* Happy birthday to you

10:17.951 --> 10:22.289
* Happy birthday to you

10:22.322 --> 10:26.359
* Happy birthday, dear...

10:26.393 --> 10:28.762
[ Overlapping names mumbled ]

10:28.796 --> 10:33.266
* Happy birthday to you

10:33.300 --> 10:36.436
So glad you guys
got to meet.

10:36.469 --> 10:37.971
That was so fun. Bye!

10:38.005 --> 10:38.939
Ben: Whoa.

10:38.972 --> 10:41.308
Hold on. I mean,
did we really get to meet?

10:41.341 --> 10:43.944
This is where I go when I don't
want to talk to my kids.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.179
This is where I go when I don't
want to talk to my parents.

10:46.213 --> 10:47.815
I just don't like
this place.

10:47.848 --> 10:49.216
Right? This place sucks.

10:49.249 --> 10:51.084
Let's disperse
and get out of here.

10:51.118 --> 10:53.186
Do you ladies think that
someone was a little nervous

10:53.220 --> 10:55.055
about me
meeting her friends

10:55.088 --> 10:55.989
and possibly,
subconsciously,

10:56.023 --> 10:57.024
picked a place that
makes it impossible

10:57.057 --> 10:59.292
for us to have any type
of human interaction?

10:59.326 --> 11:03.230
No, I think maybe someone
just likes onion volcanoes.

11:03.263 --> 11:05.899
That's exactly right, Ben.
This isn't the first time

11:05.933 --> 11:07.968
Alice has tried to avoid
mixing her worlds,

11:08.001 --> 11:10.804
but it is the first time a guy
has noticed, so I like you.

11:10.838 --> 11:12.372
Ooh, the bar downstairs
has two-for-one drinks,

11:12.405 --> 11:13.841
and you get to keep
the Buddha cup.

11:13.874 --> 11:15.342
I have 30.

11:15.375 --> 11:16.977
Well, you're about to get
one to four more

11:17.010 --> 11:18.145
depending upon how much
we all like our Buddha cups.

11:18.178 --> 11:20.047
Buddha cup!
This is happening.

11:20.080 --> 11:21.048
No.

11:21.081 --> 11:22.716
[ Zoe squeals ]

11:22.750 --> 11:25.418
**

11:25.452 --> 11:27.120
[ Groans ]

11:27.154 --> 11:30.223
Hi, Bunny.

11:30.257 --> 11:31.759
We'll have her back
after dinner.

11:31.792 --> 11:34.361
-Whatever.
-Bye.

11:34.394 --> 11:36.129
Yep, bye.
Andy: Jeff, you
just moved there.

11:36.163 --> 11:37.197
You'll meet people.

11:38.398 --> 11:40.734
Me?
Uh, I am taking this time

11:40.768 --> 11:43.036
to get to know myself.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.172
I think I'm a pretty cool guy.
Like, I see what you see in me.

11:45.205 --> 11:47.107
[ Laughs ]
All right, later, bro.

11:47.140 --> 11:48.408
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Okay.

11:48.441 --> 11:49.442
I'm heading out.

11:49.476 --> 11:50.744
Oh, okay, yeah.

11:50.778 --> 11:51.945
Have fun.

11:51.979 --> 11:52.980
[ Cellphone keys clicking ]

11:53.013 --> 11:54.181
Do you have plans tonight?

11:54.214 --> 11:56.249
I do.

11:56.283 --> 11:58.218
Oh, great.
Get ready for

11:58.251 --> 12:00.921
a supportive
handwritten letter, Jeff.

12:00.954 --> 12:02.355
[ Chuckles ]
Going old school.

12:05.392 --> 12:08.962
**

12:08.996 --> 12:11.131
And that's when I saw her,
and I knew right then and there,

12:11.164 --> 12:13.100
I got to pretend
to be a writer,

12:13.133 --> 12:15.068
schedule a fake interview, and
somehow convince her to love me.

12:15.102 --> 12:16.103
[ Both laugh ]

12:16.136 --> 12:18.005
It was weird,
but it worked.

12:18.038 --> 12:19.773
Aw.
Oh.

12:19.807 --> 12:21.108
Mm.
Cheers.

12:21.141 --> 12:23.143
Rebecca:
Cheers.
Cheers.

12:23.176 --> 12:24.778
[ Zoe whoops, giggles ]

12:24.812 --> 12:26.213
Mmm.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.048
Rebecca: And then
Alice tells the guy,

12:28.081 --> 12:30.884
"You stay away from my friend,
you creepy-ass [bleep] knuckle."

12:30.918 --> 12:32.352
[ Laughter ]

12:32.385 --> 12:34.054
He was a priest.
Oh, great.

12:34.087 --> 12:36.089
It was
a misunderstanding.

12:36.123 --> 12:37.925
Still,
such a good friend.

12:37.958 --> 12:40.193
And, uh, Bunny goes,
"Alice is fun

12:40.227 --> 12:41.895
when she isn't
breaking me."
[ Laughter ]

12:41.929 --> 12:44.164
[ Laughs ]
Sorry.

12:44.197 --> 12:45.298
I zoned out for
five seconds.

12:45.332 --> 12:46.800
What are we
laughing at?

12:46.834 --> 12:48.401
Classic Zoe.
Classic Zoe.

12:48.435 --> 12:50.203
[ Giggles, squeals ]

12:50.237 --> 12:51.538
[ Mouths ]
I love them.

12:51.571 --> 12:53.440
Well, I guess
there was another way

12:53.473 --> 12:55.275
this mixing
of the worlds could go

12:55.308 --> 12:56.977
that we didn't
even predict.

12:57.010 --> 13:01.114
They all love each other
and they all love you.

13:01.148 --> 13:02.315
I do think
the Japanese steakhouse

13:02.349 --> 13:04.051
really loosened everyone up.

13:04.084 --> 13:05.819
Gonna give myself
some credit for that.

13:05.853 --> 13:07.120
[ Both laughing ]

13:07.154 --> 13:08.388
Oh...

13:08.421 --> 13:10.190
We did it!
We did it.

13:10.223 --> 13:12.392
You met my friends --

13:12.425 --> 13:15.062
at my suggestion,
no big deal, huge deal...

13:15.095 --> 13:16.997
[ Sighs ]
...and it went great.

13:17.030 --> 13:18.999
Oh, my gosh,
it really did.

13:19.032 --> 13:20.100
[ Laughs ]
Thank you.

13:20.133 --> 13:21.168
Mmm.
Mwah.

13:21.201 --> 13:23.270
And why stop here?

13:23.303 --> 13:25.005
This may be the thrown
shrimp talking,

13:25.038 --> 13:26.439
but I'm just
gonna say it.

13:26.473 --> 13:28.541
I want to meet
your friends.

13:28.575 --> 13:31.478
[ Laughs ] Okay, sweetie.
We'll get there.

13:31.511 --> 13:34.014
Right now, you're just high
on world-mixing and MSG.

13:34.047 --> 13:36.483
No, I'm serious.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.618
We're on a roll.
Let it ride.

13:38.651 --> 13:41.388
My friends are all dorky dads.
It won't be nearly as fun.

13:41.421 --> 13:43.123
A lot of carpool talk
and hemorrhoids.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.324
I don't care.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.359
I showed you mine,
show me yours.

13:46.393 --> 13:48.561
Not your hemorrhoids,
your friends.

13:48.595 --> 13:51.064
This did go great,

13:51.098 --> 13:53.100
but just 'cause
something goes great

13:53.133 --> 13:54.501
doesn't mean
you keep doing it.

13:54.534 --> 13:57.504
You don't open
all your presents on Christmas.

13:57.537 --> 13:59.172
You do, actually.

13:59.206 --> 14:01.174
Am I not making
myself clear?

14:01.208 --> 14:05.612
I, Alice, want to
meet your friends.

14:05.645 --> 14:08.148
Do you not want
them to meet me?

14:08.181 --> 14:10.650
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

14:10.683 --> 14:12.185
-No, no.
-Hmm.

14:12.219 --> 14:13.653
You want to meet 'em?
[ Scoffs ]

14:13.686 --> 14:15.655
Let's do it.

14:15.688 --> 14:18.425
Uh, speaking of meet,
we'll have a barbecue.

14:18.458 --> 14:19.559
It'll be like
a-a meet-meat.

14:19.592 --> 14:21.962
Okay. I'm excited.

14:21.995 --> 14:26.333
[ Laughing ] Okay.
Don't try to talk me out of it.

14:26.366 --> 14:29.369
Okay, bye.

14:29.402 --> 14:31.438
Ben:
See you at the barbecue!

14:31.471 --> 14:34.307
[ Door opens, closes ]

14:34.341 --> 14:36.443
That wasn't weird, right?

14:36.476 --> 14:39.312
Weird? No. Sketchy
and suspicious? Yeah.

14:39.346 --> 14:40.580
And now that I'm sort of
running it back in my head,

14:40.613 --> 14:41.614
also weird.

14:46.186 --> 14:47.187
All right, Ben was acting
so weird about this.

14:47.220 --> 14:48.055
We got to figure out
what's going on.

14:48.088 --> 14:49.957
Alice:
Let's not freak out about it.

14:49.990 --> 14:51.124
I don't want to make
such a big deal.

14:51.158 --> 14:52.960
Maybe he was just nervous
like I was.

14:52.993 --> 14:54.461
Oh, Alice.

14:54.494 --> 14:56.429
So beautiful.
So always wrong.

14:56.463 --> 14:57.530
Hi!

14:57.564 --> 14:58.631
Hey, babe!

14:58.665 --> 15:00.667
Everyone, this is Alice.

15:00.700 --> 15:01.634
Together:
Hey, Alice.

15:01.668 --> 15:02.602
Hey, everyone.

15:02.635 --> 15:03.636
Hi.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.005
Hi.

15:05.038 --> 15:06.306
Um, so...

15:06.339 --> 15:07.640
This is my
buddy Jonathan.

15:07.674 --> 15:08.976
Nice to meet you, Alice.

15:09.009 --> 15:10.210
You, too.

15:10.243 --> 15:11.711
[ Shrieks ]
Dad, grill fire!

15:11.744 --> 15:13.546
Thank you. That's how
the meat gets cooked, Andy.

15:13.580 --> 15:15.482
No, this is different!
I know you can handle it.

15:15.515 --> 15:16.984
I know that I can't!

15:17.017 --> 15:18.685
So this is great, huh?
Maybe you should help him.

15:18.718 --> 15:20.287
-It's spreading like wildfire!
-Mm. He's fine.

15:20.320 --> 15:21.688
-I'm fine.
-[ Shouting frantically ]

15:21.721 --> 15:23.056
Okay. [ Sighs ]

15:23.090 --> 15:25.058
Dad, help!

15:25.092 --> 15:27.227
So, Jonathan,
how do you know Ben?

15:27.260 --> 15:29.029
Oh, we met
at Lincoln Park High.

15:29.062 --> 15:30.663
Oh, wow,
you must be really close.

15:30.697 --> 15:32.499
Well, we carpooled
every day.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.267
Wow. So,
tell me a crazy story

15:34.301 --> 15:36.603
about Ben from
his Lincoln Park High days.

15:36.636 --> 15:38.538
Oh, one time he found asbestos
in the girls' locker room.

15:38.571 --> 15:41.708
What was he doing
in the girls' locker room?

15:41.741 --> 15:43.376
Looking for asbestos.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.314
Oh, so you worked
at a high school together.

15:47.347 --> 15:49.549
You didn't go
to high school together.
Right.

15:49.582 --> 15:50.683
Ah.

15:50.717 --> 15:52.119
Still found
that asbestos, though.

15:52.152 --> 15:54.587
Mm. No one can take that
away from you.

15:54.621 --> 15:57.024
**

15:57.057 --> 15:58.225
I can't. No.
Andy, just take it.

16:01.594 --> 16:03.663
I'm always there for
Ben when he needs me.

16:03.696 --> 16:04.531
For anything.

16:04.564 --> 16:05.732
Aw.

16:05.765 --> 16:07.000
Drainage, roofing,

16:07.034 --> 16:09.036
sinks, Christmas lights.

16:09.069 --> 16:10.470
I'm there.

16:10.503 --> 16:12.005
**

16:12.039 --> 16:13.573
[ Chuckles ]

16:15.442 --> 16:18.311
I do a lot of foundation work
with Ben.

16:18.345 --> 16:21.214
Any chance we're talking about
a philanthropic foundation?

16:21.248 --> 16:23.050
Poured concrete.

16:23.083 --> 16:24.484
Gotcha.

16:24.517 --> 16:26.186
And how do you know Ben?

16:26.219 --> 16:27.387
Electrical.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.056
Okay. No double meaning there.
Just...

16:29.089 --> 16:30.657
-Electrical.
-Electrical.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.725
Cheers.

16:32.759 --> 16:34.761
[ Gasps ] You're not meeting
Ben's best friends.

16:34.794 --> 16:36.729
You're meeting Ben's
best subcontractors.

16:36.763 --> 16:38.698
Why doesn't he want me
to meet his real friends?

16:38.731 --> 16:40.400
What the hell
is going on here?

16:40.433 --> 16:42.269
Worst case --
He's ashamed of you,

16:42.302 --> 16:44.071
he's not as serious
as we thought,

16:44.104 --> 16:45.805
he's got another girlfriend,
and his real friends

16:45.838 --> 16:47.774
are meeting her right now!

16:47.807 --> 16:50.343
Okay, let's just ask him.

16:50.377 --> 16:53.080
And maybe we don't always
have to start with worst case.

16:53.113 --> 16:55.182
**

16:56.716 --> 16:58.318
Andy: Carlos!

16:58.351 --> 17:00.120
What's up?!
Would you like a burger?

17:00.153 --> 17:02.089
Gracias, amigo.

17:02.122 --> 17:04.757
Hey, it's nice to relax
and have fun, right?

17:04.791 --> 17:06.526
Fun is a luxury.

17:06.559 --> 17:08.728
I have to work hard
to support my family.

17:08.761 --> 17:12.065
Well, that's, uh...
fun to know.

17:12.099 --> 17:13.600
Dora:
What are you doing?

17:13.633 --> 17:15.568
Why are you hanging out
with Dad's lame co-workers?

17:15.602 --> 17:19.072
Who, Carlos? He's not lame.
He made that bench.

17:19.106 --> 17:20.773
Andy, these guys aren't
gonna be your real friends.

17:20.807 --> 17:23.243
Okay, listen, if it was
a month ago and Jeff was here,

17:23.276 --> 17:24.677
we'd be doing
who knows what...

17:24.711 --> 17:26.179
Mm-hmm.
...who knows where.

17:26.213 --> 17:28.181
Although, probably
the grillin' at this very party.

17:28.215 --> 17:29.549
Jeff loved grillin'.

17:29.582 --> 17:31.284
Okay. I can't believe
I'm saying this,

17:31.318 --> 17:33.153
but if I don't help you,
no one will.

17:35.322 --> 17:36.689
Put on something
less dorky.

17:36.723 --> 17:38.525
I'm bringing you
to my friend Megan's party.

17:38.558 --> 17:40.493
Really?

17:40.527 --> 17:41.528
Party!

17:41.561 --> 17:42.629
Yes. Okay.
Oh.

17:42.662 --> 17:44.231
Ooh. Ha.

17:44.264 --> 17:47.300
Hey, should I -- should I
box up some lemon squares?

17:47.334 --> 17:49.736
I just, I don't want
to show up empty...
Don't make me change my mind.

17:49.769 --> 17:51.571
Okay.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.440
Lemon squares?
Everything okay?

17:53.473 --> 17:55.342
Yeah.
Let the weirdness begin.

17:57.177 --> 17:59.212
Hey, babe! There you are.

17:59.246 --> 18:01.581
Having fun at this par-tay?

18:01.614 --> 18:03.183
Oh, yeah, a blast.

18:03.216 --> 18:05.585
Love meeting all your friends.
Your besties.

18:05.618 --> 18:07.520
Hi. I don't think we've met yet.
I'm Alice.

18:07.554 --> 18:09.289
Oh, uh, Ricky.
Nice to meet you.

18:09.322 --> 18:10.757
Tell me, Ricky,
where'd you meet Ben?

18:10.790 --> 18:12.359
-Well, actually, we...
-No, no. I got this.

18:12.392 --> 18:13.626
Let me guess, Ricky.
Was it on a job?

18:13.660 --> 18:14.594
Oh, sure was.

18:14.627 --> 18:16.729
Cool. What's your
favorite thing about Ben?

18:16.763 --> 18:18.465
Uh, he hires me?

18:18.498 --> 18:20.133
How many kids
does Ben have?

18:20.167 --> 18:22.335
I don't know.
How long have he and I
been dating?

18:22.369 --> 18:23.703
I thought
you were his sister.

18:23.736 --> 18:25.172
Ah.

18:25.205 --> 18:27.207
Good, Ricky.
Okay, well, please,

18:27.240 --> 18:29.709
go enjoy this
networking opportunity.

18:29.742 --> 18:30.877
Alice, um...

18:30.910 --> 18:32.445
I get it.

18:32.479 --> 18:34.481
You don't want me to meet
your real friends.

18:34.514 --> 18:35.682
Are you ashamed of me?

18:35.715 --> 18:36.883
What are you
talking about?

18:36.916 --> 18:38.485
Why aren't
our worlds mixing?

18:38.518 --> 18:40.853
Because
I don't have a world!

18:40.887 --> 18:42.555
I have no friends.

18:42.589 --> 18:44.157
I have no friends!

18:44.191 --> 18:46.459
Friends I do not have!

18:46.493 --> 18:48.728
I got married and lost
touch with old friends.

18:48.761 --> 18:50.630
I got divorced and lost touch
with the new friends.

18:50.663 --> 18:52.165
I'm down to three friends.

18:52.199 --> 18:53.466
And you've met them.

18:53.500 --> 18:55.602
My kids.
Andy, Dora, and Bunny.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.904
Three kids.
He has three kids.

18:57.937 --> 19:00.173
Too late, Ricky. Late like
you are to every damn job.

19:00.207 --> 19:01.874
So you're right, Alice.

19:01.908 --> 19:04.511
None of these people
are my friends.

19:04.544 --> 19:05.578
And you're all free to go.

19:07.547 --> 19:09.282
Go!

19:11.651 --> 19:14.187
Wow. I thought
we were friends, Ben.

19:15.855 --> 19:18.325
Great. I had one friend,
and I just pushed him away.

19:18.358 --> 19:20.227
Why didn't you
just tell me?

19:20.260 --> 19:21.761
Because after seeing
your friends

19:21.794 --> 19:24.564
and how close you guys are
and how much fun you have,

19:24.597 --> 19:26.866
I thought
I'd seem like a loser.

19:26.899 --> 19:29.469
A loser?

19:29.502 --> 19:31.504
You...

19:31.538 --> 19:33.673
Impossible.

19:33.706 --> 19:37.510
You're an amazing dad,
you're a wonderful boyfriend,

19:37.544 --> 19:39.679
you're an employer
who clearly inspires loyalty.

19:39.712 --> 19:42.849
I may have jeopardized that.
They'll get over it.

19:42.882 --> 19:45.685
You're irresistible.

19:45.718 --> 19:47.820
So...

19:47.854 --> 19:49.956
It doesn't scare you that,
outside of the kids,

19:49.989 --> 19:50.990
you're all I have?

19:51.023 --> 19:53.226
[ Whispers ]
I love it.

19:53.260 --> 19:55.895
If you have no friends,
that's one less world to mix.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.864
I mean, I'm a master
at it now, but still.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.466
Right.
Not my favorite thing.

19:59.499 --> 20:01.901
That's one way to look at it.
It's the best way.

20:01.934 --> 20:03.603
Tell me both your parents
are dead, and we're golden.

20:03.636 --> 20:05.605
One is.
Hey, we're halfway there.

20:05.638 --> 20:07.907
Sorry, that seems callous.

20:07.940 --> 20:09.409
[ Both chuckle ]

20:09.442 --> 20:11.544
[ Groans ]
Let's start fresh,

20:11.578 --> 20:13.480
and we can build a world
of friends together.

20:13.513 --> 20:15.448
We can start with mine
as a base.

20:15.482 --> 20:19.018
You know all I'm offering
is Andy, Dora, and Bunny.

20:19.051 --> 20:20.520
And eventually an ex-wife.

20:20.553 --> 20:23.390
Andy, Dora,
and Bunny are plenty.

20:23.423 --> 20:25.358
**

20:25.392 --> 20:28.395
Oh, Alice.
You're Frenching, but inside,

20:28.428 --> 20:30.563
you're thinking,
"Ex-wife?! Ex-wife?!"

20:30.597 --> 20:33.833
Oh, now, I can't wait to
meet the ex-wife.

20:33.866 --> 20:34.634
[ Laughs ]

20:38.571 --> 20:40.540
No, Andy, you know
I appreciate that, but placemats

20:40.573 --> 20:41.541
are kind of my thing.
I want to.

20:41.574 --> 20:43.276
So where am I going tonight?

20:43.310 --> 20:45.312
You aren't going anywhere.

20:45.345 --> 20:48.047
We miss you.
You're staying right here.

20:48.080 --> 20:48.915
Huh. Weird.

20:48.948 --> 20:50.650
But fun to try.

20:50.683 --> 20:52.285
[ Laughs ]

20:52.319 --> 20:53.486
Andy: I'm staying home
tonight, too.

20:53.520 --> 20:55.021
I'm worn out
from all my socializing.

20:55.054 --> 20:56.323
I brought you
to one party.

20:56.356 --> 20:57.590
And it was epic.

20:57.624 --> 20:59.926
You're so wild.
Jeff would be proud.

20:59.959 --> 21:01.461
They had a
karaoke machine,

21:01.494 --> 21:03.062
and did I sing
every Cher song?

21:03.095 --> 21:06.366
No. Because they
didn't have them all.

21:06.399 --> 21:09.669
Tou-Cher.

21:09.702 --> 21:10.670
Was it a disaster?

21:10.703 --> 21:11.704
Actually, no. I mean,
it started kind of weird,

21:11.738 --> 21:15.442
but after everyone Googled Cher,
they loved him.

21:15.475 --> 21:16.909
[ Laughs ]

21:16.943 --> 21:18.545
And you thought
I should throw away

21:18.578 --> 21:19.546
my America's
greatest divas CD.

21:19.579 --> 21:21.748
Still do.

21:21.781 --> 21:22.849
Maybe keep it
as a coaster.

21:22.882 --> 21:23.683
Okay.
